quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"Each ňĻwarnerňļ asked, ‚ÄúEven if what I brought you is better guidance than what you found your forefathers practicing?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe totally reject whatever you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  43,25,So We inflicted punishment upon them. See then what was the fate of the deniers
  43,26,"ňĻRemember, O Prophetňļ when Abraham declared to his father and his people, ‚ÄúI am totally free of whatever ňĻgodsňļ you worship"
  43,27,"except the One Who originated me, and He will surely guide me.‚ÄĚ"
  43,28,"And he left this enduring declaration among his descendants, so they may ňĻalwaysňļ turn back ňĻto Godňļ"
  43,29,"In fact, I had allowed enjoyment for these ňĻMeccansňļ and their forefathers, until the truth came to them along with a messenger making things clear"
  43,30,"ňĻButňļ when the truth came to them, they said, ‚ÄúThis is magic, and we totally reject it.‚ÄĚ"
  43,31,"And they exclaimed, ‚ÄúIf only this Quran was revealed to a great man from ňĻone ofňļ the two cities!‚ÄĚ"
  43,32,Is it they who distribute your Lord‚Äôs mercy? We ňĻaloneňļ have distributed their ňĻveryňļ livelihood among them in this worldly life and raised some of them in rank above others so that some may employ others in service. ňĻButňļ your Lord‚Äôs mercy is far better than whatever ňĻwealthňļ they amass
  43,33,"Were it not that people might ňĻbe tempted toňļ become one community ňĻof disbelieversňļ, We would have supplied the homes of ňĻonlyňļ those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate with silver roofs and ňĻsilverňļ stairways to ascend"
  43,34,as well as ňĻsilverňļ gates and thrones to recline on
  43,35,and ornaments ňĻof goldňļ. Yet all this is no more than a ňĻfleetingňļ enjoyment in this worldly life. ňĻButňļ the Hereafter with your Lord is ňĻonlyňļ for those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  43,36,"And whoever turns a blind eye to the Reminder of the Most Compassionate, We place at the disposal of each a devilish one as their close associate"
  43,37,who will certainly hinder them from the ňĻRightňļ Way while they think they are ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  43,38,"But when such a person comes to Us, one will say ňĻto their associateňļ, ‚ÄúI wish you were as distant from me as the east is from the west! What an evil associate ňĻyou wereňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  43,39,"ňĻIt will be said to both,ňļ ‚ÄúSince you all did wrong, sharing in the punishment will be of no benefit to you this Day.‚ÄĚ"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind or those clearly astray"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away ňĻfrom this worldňļ, We will surely inflict punishment upon them"
  43,42,"Or if We show you what We threaten them with, We certainly have full power over them"
  43,43,So hold firmly to what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ. You are truly on the Straight Path
  43,44,Surely this ňĻQuranňļ is a glory for you and your people. And you will ňĻallňļ be questioned ňĻabout itňļ
  43,45,Ask ňĻthe followers ofňļ the messengers that We already sent before you if We ňĻeverňļ appointed ňĻotherňļ gods to be worshipped besides the Most Compassionate
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said: ‚ÄúI am a messenger of the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"although every sign We showed them was greater than the one before.¬†Ultimately, We seized them with torments so that they might return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  43,49,"ňĻThenňļ they pleaded, ‚ÄúO ňĻmightyňļ magician! Pray to your Lord on our behalf, by virtue of the covenant He made with you.¬†We will certainly accept guidance.‚ÄĚ"
  43,50,"But as soon as We removed the torments from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh called out to his people, boasting, ‚ÄúO my people! Am I not sovereign over Egypt as well as ňĻallňļ these streams¬†flowing at my feet? Can you not see"
  43,52,Am I not better than this nobody who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Why then have no golden bracelets ňĻof kingshipňļ been granted to him or angels come with him as escorts!‚ÄĚ
  43,54,"And so he fooled his people, and they obeyed him. They were truly a rebellious people"
  43,55,"So when they enraged Us, We inflicted punishment upon them, drowning them all"
  43,56,And We made them an example and a lesson for those after them